[1] Liberia, Sierra Leone: Nigerian Ebola medical volunteers fly in
Date: Fri 5 Dec 2014
Source: Reuters [edited]
http://www.reuters.com/article/2014/12/05/us-health-ebola-idUSKCN0JJ0ZX20141205


Nigerian Ebola medical volunteers fly into Liberia, Sierra Leone
----------------------------------------------------------------
More than 175 Nigerian medics arrived in Liberia and Sierra Leone on Friday [5 Dec 2014] to join the fight against Ebola, the 1st of 600 volunteers promised by the regional giant, which had contained its own outbreak earlier this year. Months into the Ebola response, experts say they are still short of medical personnel to staff treatment centers. "This is the African spirit you are showing, this is the Nigerian spirit," Nigeria's ambassador to Liberia, Chigozie Obi-Nnadozie, told 76 Nigerian medics who landed there. Another 100 medical volunteers landed in Freetown, Sierra Leone.

The medics will boost weak local health systems that are also struggling to contain other preventable diseases, as Ebola discourages people from going to clinics for fear of becoming Ebola infected. UN child agency UNICEF on Friday began a campaign to provide 2.4 million people in Sierra Leone with anti-malarial drugs to ease the strain on the healthcare system and allow Ebola cases to be identified more easily. The 2 diseases have similar symptoms, including headaches, fever and aching joints.... -- more

[Byline: James Harding Giahyue and Umaru Fofana]

